enableMotor.title: Use Motor
enableMotor.description: Enable a motor to power the automatic rotation around the hinge axis.

limits.title: Limits
limits.description: Low and high angular limits for the constraint in degrees. By default, low is greater than high meaning no limits.

softness.title: Softness
softness.description: Softness of the constraint. Recommend 0.8 to 1. Describes the percentage of limits where movement is free. Beyond this softness percentage, the limit is gradually enforced until the "hard" (1.0) limit is reached.

biasFactor.title: Bias Factor
biasFactor.description: Bias factor of the constraint. Recommend 0.3 +/- approximately 0.3. Strength with which constraint resists zeroth order (angular, not angular velocity) limit violation.

relaxationFactor.title: Relaxation Factor
relaxationFactor.description: Relaxation factor of the constraint. Recommend to keep this near 1. The lower the value, the less the constraint will fight velocities which violate the angular limits.

breakingThreshold.title: Break Threshold
breakingThreshold.description: Maximum breaking impulse threshold required to break the constraint.

enableCollision.title: Enable Collision
enableCollision.description: Enable collision between linked rigid bodies.

swingSpan1.title: Swing 1 Limit
swingSpan1.description: The Swing 1 Limit limits the rotation around the swing axis. Swing 1 Limit limits an axis of rotation orthogonal to the twist axis and Swing Limit 2. The limit angle is symmetric. Therefore, a value of 20 will limit the rotation between -20 and 20 degrees.

swingSpan2.title: Swing 2 Limit
swingSpan2.description: The Swing 2 Limit limits the rotation around the swing axis. Swing 2 Limit limits an axis of rotation orthogonal to the twist axis and Swing Limit 1. The limit angle is symmetric. Therefore, a value of 20 will limit the rotation between -20 and 20 degrees.

twistSpan.title: Twist Limit
twistSpan.description: The Twist Limit limits the rotation around the twist axis. The limit angle is symmetric. Therefore, a value of 20 will limit the twist rotation between -20 and 20 degrees.

baseEntity.title: Base Entity
baseEntity.description: Image Element Entity that shows the base of the joystick.

nubEntity.title: Nub Entity
nubEntity.description: Image Element Entity that shows the nub (top) of the joystick.

order: Move to first touch and fixed
Move to first touch and drags

type.title: Type
type.description: Set type of behavior for the joystick.

hideOnRelease.title: Hide on Release
hideOnRelease.description: Will only show the joystick when the user is using it and will hide it on touch end. This is commonly used if you don't want the joystick to block what's being shown on screen.

identifier.title: Idenitifier
identifier.description: A unique name for the joystick to refer to it by in the API. Will give a warning in browser tools if the name is not unique.

axisDeadZone.title: Axis Dead Zone
axisDeadZone.description: The number of UI units from the position of the Base Entity where input is not registered.

axisRange.title: Axis Range
axisRange.description: The number of UI units from the position of the Base Entity that the Nub Entity can move to and is the maximum range

positionOnRelease.title: Position on Release
positionOnRelease.description: Where to move the joystick on release and can help keep the screen tidy so that there are clear areas to show the game and arrange controls.

vibrationPress.title: Vibration duration (ms)
vibrationPress.description: If the device supports vibration with 'Navigator.vibrate', it will vibrate for the duration set here on touch down.Set to 0 to disable.

identifier.title: Identifier
identifier.description: A unique name for the button to refer to it by in the API. Will give a warning in browser tools if the name is not unique.

vibration.title: Vibration duration (ms)
vibration.description: If the device supports vibration with 'Navigator.vibrate', it will vibrate for the duration set here on touch down.Set to 0 to disable.
